==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Moringa
<hw>Mo*rin"ga</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <ety>[Malayam
<ets>murunggi</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of trees of
Southern India and Northern Africa. One species (<spn>Moringa
pterygosperma</spn>) is the horse-radish tree, and its seeds, as well as
those of <spn>Moringa aptera</spn>, are known in commerce as
<prod>ben</prod> or <prod>ben nuts</prod>, and yield the oil called
<prod>oil of ben</prod>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Moringic</ent>⟦br⟧
